ZH: 他常常编造一些谎言来骗人。
EN: He often fabricates lies to deceive people.

ZH: 她编造了一个离奇的故事来吸引别人的注意。
EN: She made up a bizarre story to capture other people's attention.

ZH: 不要随便编造事实。
EN: Don't make up facts casually.

ZH: 这个小孩非常擅长编造故事。
EN: This kid is very good at making up stories.

ZH: 他编造了一个看起来非常真实的理由。
EN: He fabricated a reason that looked very believable.

ZH: 她的证词是编造的，毫无根据。
EN: Her testimony was fabricated and baseless.

ZH: 这篇文章被指控编造事实。
EN: This article is accused of fabricating facts.

ZH: 这是一则编造的新闻报道。
EN: This is a fabricated news report.

ZH: 他编造了一套复杂的谎言来掩盖真相。
EN: He fabricated a complex set of lies to cover the truth.

ZH: 别人的闲言碎语不能成为我们编造谎言的理由。
EN: Others' idle gossip cannot become a reason for us to fabricate lies.

ZH: 请不要编造关于我的传言。
EN: Please do not fabricate rumors about me.

ZH: 警察怀疑他编造了整个事件。
EN: The police suspect that he fabricated the entire incident.

ZH: 他是一个善于编造理由逃避责任的人。
EN: He is someone who is good at fabricating reasons to avoid responsibility.

ZH: 不要轻易相信别人编造的谎言。
EN: Do not easily believe in fabricated lies by others.

ZH: 这篇报道涉嫌编造事实。
EN: This report is suspected of fabricating facts.

ZH: 他的证言被证明是编造的。
EN: His testimony was proven to be fabricated.

ZH: 这部小说是根据真实事件改编的，没有编造。
EN: This novel is based on a true event, not fabricated.

ZH: 学术研究必须避免编造数据。
EN: Academic research must avoid fabricating data.

ZH: 他因为编造谎言而被解雇。
EN: He was dismissed because he fabricated lies.

ZH: 他为了掩饰自己的错误编造了一个借口。
EN: He fabricated an excuse to cover up his mistake.
